MIA TRACON called to report that security for Turkey Point Nuclear Power Plant had called them to report UAS activity over the facility. Turkey Point Power Plant is located 4NM SE of HST. HQ DEN took the name and number of the Security Company that works security for the plant. 0058 HQ DEN contacted Turkey Point Security. The Security Officer reported that they had 3 drones operating over the facility for roughly 50 minutes (1905-1950). The drones have since moved on, 2 went east over the water and one went west. Turkey Point Security disclosed they contacted HST and MIA to try to verify if the Facilities were aware of any approved drone operations with negative results. They also called the USCG to see if they could assist with the drones over the water. The drones were 3x3 ft with flashing red and white lights. HQ DEN checked with SOSC and confirmed there were no approved UAS operations in that area. HQ DEN then recommended Turkey Point Security contact Miami Dade 305-5985-6263 and report the drones and request their assistance in locating the operators of the UAS. Turkey Point Security also said they had a FBI number 305-944-9101 and HQ DEN recommended they make that report to them as well. 0120 Turkey Point Security made contact with Miami-Dade PD and they were going to send an officer out to take a report. HQ DEN left our direct number and requested Turkey Point Security contact us directly with any further updates.

SUMMARY.CEDAR: KFB961 reported a 'narrow miss' with a drone at 030 off the right side, southbound.
QAFINDINGS.CEDAR: An analysis of the event was completed by reviewing the MOR Summary, related MORs: SNA-M-2021/07/12-0001 / SNA-M-2021/07/12-0002 / SNA-M-2021/07/12-0003 (disabled A/C on runway and Go Around), Nasquest and Falcon Playback. KFB961 reported a NMAC with a UAS, 4+ rotors, the size of an office chair. No UAS advisories were heard being issued other than to the aircraft that originally reported the NMAC. NMAC N-WP-R-SCT-21-005 filed. SCT made no notifications made regarding the UAS report. P Roberts  7/28/2021

SUMMARY.CEDAR: N194SV reported a drone roughly 3 miles southwest of the field after landing. N194SV turned away from the field and then re-joined the final, then landed without incident.
QAFINDINGS.CEDAR: Facility summary, weather and falcon bookmark reviewed. N194SV was at 1,800ft 3 miles southwest of PIE when the aircraft encountered a drone 100ft above the aircraft. Evasive maneuvers were taken to avoid the object. The pilot reported "it passed right over us" and "couldn't have been more than 100ft" above the aircraft. The aircraft landed without further incident and made the report to ATC after landing. ATIS was updated and advisories were broadcasted on the frequency with no further sightings reported. DEN, ROC and law enforcement notified. Preliminary NMAC filed.

REMARKS: Aircraft observed a UAS while west bound at 2,600 feet, 4 NM north of SAV. No evasive action was taken. LEO notified.
SUMMARY.CEDAR: END4689 CRJ9 was at 026 downwind to SAV reported a drone approximately 400 feet below out their window, no direction was given. No evasive maneuvers were necessary. END4689 landed without incident. Chatham County Police were notified. Drone was medium size with black props white in color. Drone position off the SAV VORTAC 350 radial 4 DME.
